      • setElementCountThreshold

        public abstract BundlingSettings.Builder setElementCountThreshold(Integer elementCountThreshold)
        Set the element count threshold to use for bundling. After this many elements are accumulated, they will be wrapped up in a bundle and sent.

      • setElementCountLimit

        public abstract BundlingSettings.Builder setElementCountLimit(Integer elementCountLimit)
        Set the element count limit to use for bundling. Any individual requests with more than this many elements will be rejected outright, and bundles will not be formed with more than this many elements.

      • setRequestByteThreshold

        public abstract BundlingSettings.Builder setRequestByteThreshold(Integer requestByteThreshold)
        Set the request byte threshold to use for bundling. After this many bytes are accumulated, the elements will be wrapped up in a bundle and sent.

      • setRequestByteLimit

        public abstract BundlingSettings.Builder setRequestByteLimit(Integer requestByteLimit)
        Set the request byte limit to use for bundling. Any individual requests with more than this many bytes will be rejected outright, and bundles will not be formed with more than this many bytes.

      • setDelayThreshold

        public abstract BundlingSettings.Builder setDelayThreshold(org.joda.time.Duration delayThreshold)
        Set the delay threshold to use for bundling. After this amount of time has elapsed (counting from the first element added), the elements will be wrapped up in a bundle and sent.

      • setBlockingCallCountThreshold

        public abstract BundlingSettings.Builder setBlockingCallCountThreshold(Integer blockingCallCountThreshold)
        Set the blocking call count threshold for bundling. After this many blocking calls are made, the elements will be wrapped up in a bundle and sent. This defaults to 1. Do not set this to a number higher than the number of threads that are capable of blocking on the bundler, or else your application will suffer dead time while it waits for the delay threshold to trip.
